Next, we implement the methods declared in the header file in `UndergraduateStudent.cpp`. This includes the constructor, accessor and mutator methods, and the display method. The constructor will validate inputs, such as ensuring GPA is within a valid range (e.g., 0.0 to 4.0).

```cpp
#include "UndergraduateStudent.h"
#include <iostream>

UndergraduateStudent::UndergraduateStudent(const std::string& name, const std::string& id, double initialGPA)
    : fullName(name), studentID(id), gpa(initialGPA) {
    if (gpa < 0.0 || gpa > 4.0) {
        std::cerr << "Invalid GPA value. Setting GPA to 0.0." << std::endl;
        gpa = 0.0;
    }
}

